[{"id":"a","description":"Create scripts/smoke_narrative.py in the cypherclaw repo: a small CLI that loads the Deniable Tailscale base URL from env (NARRATIVE_BASE_URL, default http://cypherclaw:<port>), then performs GET /healthz and GET /readyz, printing status code and short body for each. Exit non-zero on any non-2xx. Use only stdlib (urllib + argparse). No auth handling beyond optional --token bearer header.","tier":"T1"},{"id":"b","description":"Extend scripts/smoke_narrative.py to also exercise the remaining narrative-api endpoints (entity list/get and any narrative generation/read endpoints currently exposed). Use minimal valid payloads or known-safe IDs; on each call print METHOD PATH -> status in one line. Add a --verbose flag that also prints first 200 chars of body. Keep total runtime under ~5s against a reachable server.","tier":"T1"},{"id":"c","description":"Add a 'Smoke test from Deniable' section to the cypherclaw repo README documenting: prerequisites (Tailscale connected to cypherclaw, NARRATIVE_BASE_URL env var), exact invocation (`python scripts/smoke_narrative.py` and `--verbose`), expected output shape, and exit-code semantics. Include a one-line troubleshooting note pointing to Tailscale status if connection fails.","tier":"T1"},{"id":"d","description":"Run scripts/smoke_narrative.py against a local/dev narrative-api instance to confirm it executes end-to-end and exits 0 on a healthy server and non-zero when the server is down. Capture the run output into sdp/logs/ as evidence and note the result in run-log.md. No code changes unless smoke run reveals a bug in the script itself.","tier":"T1"}]
